Maybe there are some crossed wires here.  The KL10 and KS10 were the only
-10s that REQUIRED a little front-end computer to provide console services.
But KIs often used front-end PDP-11s called DN87 to provide terminal lines
and other remote services.  *I* call these systems "front-ends" too.
An earlier version of the front-end, called the DN92, I think, was based on
a PDP-8.  Earlier -10s used a hardwired device called a DC10 to provide
the terminal connectivity.

I'm not sure which ones of these could have been used by a KA10.
