For those of you who don't know what we're talking about the RP-02
used a linear motor to move the head assembly. There was a rack
machined with teeth spaced 0.02 in. apart. There were two pawls offset
by 0.01 in. arranged such that either one or the other of them would
mesh with a few teeth and hold the head assembly in place. There were
203 cylinders 0.01 in apart. A bank of RP02's up close would make
quite a racket.

I had to test a maximum configuration of 8 for weeks in the mill on
floor 5-0, below milll pond level and untouched by sunlight. But
that's another story.





